#: ../../advanced_concepts.md:136
msgid "Record a screencast"
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_concepts.md:138
msgid ""
"After you've built a Streamlit app, you may want to discuss some of it "
"with co-workers over email or Slack, or share it with the world on "
"Twitter. A great way to do that is with Streamlit's built-in screencast "
"recorder. With it, you can record, narrate, stop, save, and share with a "
"few clicks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_concepts.md:140
msgid ""
"To start a screencast, locate the menu in the upper right corner of your "
"app (☰), select Record a screencast, and follow the prompts. Before the "
"recording starts, you'll see a countdown — this means it's showtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_concepts.md:142
msgid ""
"To stop your screencast, go back to the menu (☰) and select Stop "
"recording (or hit the ESC key). Follow the prompts to preview your "
"recording and save it to disk. That's it, you're ready to share your "
"Streamlit app."
msgstr ""

